ALTER TABLE = main command
MODIFY = one option inside ALTER TABLE

🔧 What is ALTER TABLE?

Used to change the structure of a table

We can:

Add column
Drop column
Rename column
Change datatype

What is MODIFY?
Used to change column definition (datatype, size, etc.)
It is part of ALTER TABLE, not separate command

Example

✅ ALTER TABLE (general use)
ALTER TABLE students
ADD email VARCHAR(100);

Adds new column

✅ MODIFY (inside ALTER TABLE)
ALTER TABLE students
MODIFY name VARCHAR(100);

Changes column size/type

LTER = change table
MODIFY = change column inside table

Pro Tip

Different databases use slightly different words:

MySQL → MODIFY
SQL Server → ALTER COLUMN

Example:

ALTER TABLE students
ALTER COLUMN name VARCHAR(100);
